chunk_content: These “enhanced TB screening” approaches recommended by the WHO may use CXR or mWRD alone or in combination with WHO four-symptom screening (W4SS) to optimize TB case detection among people living with HIV (PLHIV), including those who are asymptomatic. Patients who are screened using W4SS alone should be reported under the ‘Symptom Screen’ disaggregate. 168 Further information on how to use and collect these data is provided by WHO in the following guidelines: “Latent Tuberculosis Infection: Updated and Consolidated Guidelines for Programmatic Management.” T R How to review for Only one disaggregation type is used for age (fine disaggregates).
